               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18421128-name-1183" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18421128-name-1183" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18421128-name-1183" type="surname" value="SUMNER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18421128-name-1183" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM SUMNER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am in the service of William Hindley, cheese<lb></lb>monger, Gray's-inn-lane. On the 19th of Nov. I saw the prisoner outside the shop—there was a stall-board inside the window, which was open—I saw the prisoner take a piece of bacon up, look at it, and walk away with it—I went out, brought her back with it, and gave her into custody—this is. the bacon—it is my master's.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18421128-name-1184" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18421128-name-1184" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18421128-name-1184" type="surname" value="HAYWARD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18421128-name-1184" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>HENRY HAYWARD</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable C</hi> 97.) I took the prisoner, and have the bacon.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> My husband had 12<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. in the Savings' Bank—he drew it out, and stopped out three nights drinking—I was a whole fortnight looking for him—some persons gave me drink, I went on to Gray's-inn-lane, and a woman said, "Mrs. Cameron, there is a bit of bacon for you"—I knew nothing more till I was in the station next morning.</p>
